N2  - This study focuses on workers' responses to job dissatisfaction. It is suggested that four theoretical categories?exit, voice, loyalty, and neglect?characterize a diverse group of more specific behaviors (e.g., turnover, absenteeism, lateness, talking to supervisor, requesting a transfer). A multidimensional scaling analysis (MDS) of collected data supports the categories.
AB  - This study focuses on workers' responses to job dissatisfaction. It is suggested that four theoretical categories?exit, voice, loyalty, and neglect?characterize a diverse group of more specific behaviors (e.g., turnover, absenteeism, lateness, talking to supervisor, requesting a transfer). A multidimensional scaling analysis (MDS) of collected data supports the categories.
