N2  - Patterns of investment in expansion and/or replacement of equipment by strategic business units of U.S. companies in the PIMS data base were analyzed, using a hierarchical framework that assumes that investment decisions are made at two levels: the business level and the corporate level. Strong empirical support was found for the postulated hierarchical framework.
